 {{ubl|French|[[Antillean Creole]]}} }} '''''Creole Connections''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Nous près, nous loin'''}})<ref name=ijsl/> is a 1986 Canadian documentary film produced by Montreal's [[InformAction]], profiling the [[Antillean Creole|Creole language]] and culture in the [[Lesser Antilles]].<ref name=informaction/> Its title comes from a song by [[Martinique]] singer [[Dédé Saint Prix]].<ref name=ijsl/> The film was shot in 1984 across four territories: [[Dominica]], [[Guadeloupe]], Martinique and [[Saint Lucia]].<ref name=ijsl/><ref name=cine-ca/>
