{{notability|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox journal | title = Italian Americana | image = 2018 Ital Am cover.png | abbreviation = Ital. Am. | editor = Carla A. Simonini | frequency = Biannual | publisher = [[Youngstown State University]] | country = United States | history = 1974-present | website = http://italianamericana.ysu.edu/ | link2 = http://italianamericana.ysu.edu/wordpress/index.php/category/archived-journals/ | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0096-8846 | OCLC = 891511663 | LCCN = 75641589 }} '''''Italian Americana''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering studies on the [[Italian Americans|Italian-American]] experience. It publishes history, fiction, memoirs, poetry, and reviews.<ref name="history" /> The [[editor-in-chief]] is Carla A. Simonini ([[Youngstown State University]]).
==History== The journal was established in 1974 by [[Richard Gambino]], Ernest Falbo, and Bruno Arcudi under the auspices of [[Queens College, City University of New York]], where Gambino taught.<ref name="history">{{cite web |website=Youngstown State University |title=History of Italian Americana |url=http://italianamericana.ysu.edu/wordpress/index.php/our-history/ |access-date=September 23, 2017}}</ref> In 1989, [[Carol Bonomo Albright]] became editor, and the journal was published by the [[University of Rhode Island]]. Other notable editors have included novelist [[Christine Palamidessi Moore]] and poets [[Michael Palma]] and [[Maria Terrone]]. Simonini became editor in 2015, and the journal moved to [[Youngstown State University]].<ref name="history" /><ref>{{cite book |last1=Albright |first1=Carol Bonomo |authorlink=Carol Bonomo Albright |last2=Herman |first2=Joanna Clapps |authorlink2=Joanna Clapps Herman |title=Wild Dreams: The Best of Italian Americana |publisher=Fordham University Press |date=2008 |isbn=9780823229109 |pages=1–2 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dCI6PNEYHZEC&pg=PA1}}</ref>
